<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>Myles Braithwaite: weblog entries tagged in Snippet.</title><link>http://mylesbraithwaite.com/blog/tag/Snippet/</link><description>Hoping for the Best, Imagining the Worst.</description><atom:link href="http://mylesbraithwaite.com/feeds/blog/tag/snippet/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en-ca</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 24 Nov 2010 00:00:00 -0500</lastBuildDate><item><title>How to find if a directory or file exists in Bash</title><link>http://mylesbraithwaite.com/blog/2010/nov/24/how-find-if-directory-or-file-exists-bash/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;This is a quick service announcement on how to find if a directory or file exists in Bash.&lt;/p&gt;
